<section class="section-white" id="day-trips">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header centered reveal">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">Eleven Adventures</span>
      <h2 class="section-title">Pick Your Tanzania Day Trip</h2>
      <p class="section-lead" style="margin-top:12px">Each trip below runs as a complete day from pickup to drop-off. Starting prices are per person. Tap a card for the full itinerary, highlights, and what is included.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="dest-grid" style="grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fill,minmax(320px,1fr))">
      <article class="dest-card reveal" id="tarangire-safari-tour">
        <div class="dest-visual">
          <img src="/images/daytrip-tarangire.jpg" alt="Elephant herd at Tarangire National Park" width="800" height="500" loading="lazy">
          <span class="trip-price">From $245 Per person</span>
        </div>
        <div class="dest-body">
          <div class="dest-tags"><span class="dest-tag">Tarangire</span><span class="dest-tag">Day Trip</span></div>
          <h3 class="dest-name">Tarangire Safari Tour</h3>
          <p class="dest-desc">Escape into a beautifully rugged wilderness defined by massive ancient baobab trees and iconic African landscapes. This day trip takes you into one of Tanzania&#39;s most dynamic seasonal parks, famous for its raw, untamed atmosphere and exceptional wildlife concentrations.</p>
          <a href="/daytrips/tarangire" class="dest-cta" style="margin-top:14px;display:inline-flex">See full itinerary &amp; details &#x2192;</a>
        </div>
      </article>
      <article class="dest-card reveal" id="materuni-waterfall-and-coffee-farm-tour">
        <div class="dest-visual"><img src="/images/daytrip-materuni.jpg" alt="Materuni Falls near Moshi, on the lower slopes of Mount Kilimanjaro" width="800" height="500" loading="lazy"><span class="trip-price">From $91 Per person</span></div>
        <div class="dest-body">
          <div class="dest-tags"><span class="dest-tag">Kilimanjaro</span><span class="dest-tag">Day Trip</span></div>
          <h3 class="dest-name">Materuni Waterfall and Coffee Farm Tour</h3>
          <p class="dest-desc">Immerse yourself in local culture and lush landscapes on the fertile lower slopes of Mount Kilimanjaro. This day trip combines a scenic hike through a green paradise to a stunning 80-meter waterfall with a hands-on, authentic look into the traditional coffee-making process of the Chagga people.</p>
          <a href="/daytrips/materuni-waterfall-coffee" class="dest-cta" style="margin-top:14px;display:inline-flex">See full itinerary &amp; details &#x2192;</a>
        </div>
      </article>
      <article class="dest-card reveal" id="arusha-safari">
        <div class="dest-visual">
          <img src="/images/daytrip-arusha.jpg" alt="Arusha National Park with Mount Meru" width="800" height="500" loading="lazy">
          <span class="trip-price">From $263 Per person</span>
        </div>
        <div class="dest-body">
          <div class="dest-tags"><span class="dest-tag">Arusha</span><span class="dest-tag">Day Trip</span></div>
          <h3 class="dest-name">Arusha Safari</h3>
          <p class="dest-desc">Perfect for travelers seeking a diverse and active safari experience without spending hours on the road. Located just a short drive from the city center, Arusha National Park packs a staggering variety of ecosystems, from dense montane rainforests to jagged volcanic cones and alkaline lakes, into a compact space.</p>
          <a href="/daytrips/arusha-national-park" class="dest-cta" style="margin-top:14px;display:inline-flex">See full itinerary &amp; details &#x2192;</a>
        </div>
      </article>
      <article class="dest-card reveal" id="ol-doinyo-lengai">
        <div class="dest-visual">
          <img src="/images/daytrip-natron.jpg" alt="Ol Doinyo Lengai volcano near Lake Natron" width="800" height="500" loading="lazy">
          <span class="trip-price">From $1,141 Per person</span>
        </div>
        <div class="dest-body">
          <div class="dest-tags"><span class="dest-tag">Lake Natron</span><span class="dest-tag">Day Trip</span></div>
          <h3 class="dest-name">Ol Doinyo Lengai</h3>
          <p class="dest-desc">An intense, off-the-beaten-path expedition to the active stratovolcano revered by the Maasai as the &#39;Mountain of God.&#39; Rising sharply from the arid floor of the Rift Valley near Lake Natron, this challenging day trek is a steep, demanding ascent designed for adventurous climbers seeking raw volcanic geology and surreal landscapes.</p>
          <a href="/daytrips/ol-doinyo-lengai" class="dest-cta" style="margin-top:14px;display:inline-flex">See full itinerary &amp; details &#x2192;</a>
        </div>
      </article>
      <article class="dest-card reveal" id="kilimanjaro-helicopter-tour">
        <div class="dest-visual"><img src="/images/daytrip-helicopter.jpg" alt="Aerial view of Mount Kilimanjaro from above the clouds" width="800" height="500" loading="lazy"><span class="trip-price">From $3,500 Per person</span></div>
        <div class="dest-body">
          <div class="dest-tags"><span class="dest-tag">Kilimanjaro</span><span class="dest-tag">Day Trip</span></div>
          <h3 class="dest-name">Kilimanjaro Helicopter Tour</h3>
          <p class="dest-desc">Experience the ultimate luxury adventure and skip the grueling multi-day trek to see the rooftop of Africa. This exclusive scenic flight lifts you high above the clouds, providing a thrilling, birds-eye perspective of Mount Kilimanjaro&#39;s majestic snow-capped peaks, dramatic volcanic craters, and ancient glacial walls.</p>
          <a href="/daytrips/kilimanjaro-helicopter-tour" class="dest-cta" style="margin-top:14px;display:inline-flex">See full itinerary &amp; details &#x2192;</a>
        </div>
      </article>
      <article class="dest-card reveal" id="lake-chala">
        <div class="dest-visual"><img src="/images/daytrip-chala.jpg" alt="Lake Chala, a volcanic crater lake on the Tanzania and Kenya border" width="800" height="500" loading="lazy"><span class="trip-price">From $118 Per person</span></div>
        <div class="dest-body">
          <div class="dest-tags"><span class="dest-tag">Kilimanjaro</span><span class="dest-tag">Day Trip</span></div>
          <h3 class="dest-name">Lake Chala</h3>
          <p class="dest-desc">Discover a hidden paradise tucked away on the border of Tanzania and Kenya. Lake Chala is a deep, pristine volcanic crater lake fed entirely by clean, underground springs from Mount Kilimanjaro. Surrounded by lush, steep green crater walls, it offers a tranquil oasis perfect for hiking, birdwatching, and peaceful relaxation away from safari crowds.</p>
          <a href="/daytrips/lake-chala" class="dest-cta" style="margin-top:14px;display:inline-flex">See full itinerary &amp; details &#x2192;</a>
        </div>
      </article>
      <article class="dest-card reveal" id="ndarakwai-ranch">
        <div class="dest-visual"><img src="/images/daytrip-ndarakwai.jpg" alt="Plains zebras on Tanzanian savanna at sunrise" width="800" height="500" loading="lazy"><span class="trip-price">From $191 Per person</span></div>
        <div class="dest-body">
          <div class="dest-tags"><span class="dest-tag">Kilimanjaro</span><span class="dest-tag">Day Trip</span></div>
          <h3 class="dest-name">Ndarakwai Ranch</h3>
          <p class="dest-desc">Explore a pioneering model for community-based conservation on the western slopes of Mount Kilimanjaro. Ndarakwai Ranch is a privately owned, 11,000-acre ranch dedicated to restoring self-sustaining habitats that had been degraded by overgrazing. It offers a unique, intimate wilderness experience where you can see wildlife recovery firsthand.</p>
          <a href="/daytrips/ndarakwai-ranch" class="dest-cta" style="margin-top:14px;display:inline-flex">See full itinerary &amp; details &#x2192;</a>
        </div>
      </article>
      <article class="dest-card reveal" id="chemka-hot-springs">
        <div class="dest-visual"><img src="/images/daytrip-chemka.jpg" alt="Kikuletwa Hot Springs turquoise pools surrounded by fig trees" width="800" height="500" loading="lazy"><span class="trip-price">From $85 Per person</span></div>
        <div class="dest-body">
          <div class="dest-tags"><span class="dest-tag">Kilimanjaro</span><span class="dest-tag">Day Trip</span></div>
          <h3 class="dest-name">Chemka Hot Springs</h3>
          <p class="dest-desc">Unwind in an enchanting desert oasis hidden within an arid scrubland plain. Chemka Hot Springs (also known as Kikuletwa) features beautiful pools of warm, crystal-clear turquoise water surrounded by a dense canopy of ancient fig trees and twisting roots. It is the perfect tropical paradise for swimming, relaxing, and refreshing your body after a dusty safari or a grueling mountain trek.</p>
          <a href="/daytrips/chemka-hot-springs" class="dest-cta" style="margin-top:14px;display:inline-flex">See full itinerary &amp; details &#x2192;</a>
        </div>
      </article>
      <article class="dest-card reveal" id="mount-kilimanjaro-day-hikes">
        <div class="dest-visual"><img src="/images/daytrip-dayhike.jpg" alt="Lush montane rainforest trail on Mount Kilimanjaro" width="800" height="500" loading="lazy"><span class="trip-price">From $712 Per person</span></div>
        <div class="dest-body">
          <div class="dest-tags"><span class="dest-tag">Kilimanjaro</span><span class="dest-tag">Day Trip</span></div>
          <h3 class="dest-name">Mount Kilimanjaro Day Hikes</h3>
          <p class="dest-desc">Walk in the footsteps of legends without committing to an arduous week-long trek. This day hike takes you through the historic Marangu Gate and leads you up into the enchanted, mist-shrouded montane rainforest belt of Mount Kilimanjaro National Park, allowing you to experience the magic of the world&#39;s tallest free-standing mountain in a single day.</p>
          <a href="/daytrips/kilimanjaro-day-hike" class="dest-cta" style="margin-top:14px;display:inline-flex">See full itinerary &amp; details &#x2192;</a>
        </div>
      </article>
      <article class="dest-card reveal" id="horseback-riding">
        <div class="dest-visual"><img src="/images/daytrip-horseback.jpg" alt="Riders on horseback crossing an open grassland" width="800" height="500" loading="lazy"><span class="trip-price">From $120 Per person</span></div>
        <div class="dest-body">
          <div class="dest-tags"><span class="dest-tag">Arusha</span><span class="dest-tag">Day Trip</span></div>
          <h3 class="dest-name">Horseback Riding</h3>
          <p class="dest-desc">Experience the freedom of the African bush from a completely unique perspective. Located on an exclusive wildlife estate just outside Arusha town, this horseback riding day trip allows you to ride gently alongside plains game, moving quietly through scenery without the noise and disruption of a traditional safari vehicle.</p>
          <a href="/daytrips/horseback-riding" class="dest-cta" style="margin-top:14px;display:inline-flex">See full itinerary &amp; details &#x2192;</a>
        </div>
      </article>
      <article class="dest-card reveal" id="arusha-shopping-tour">
        <div class="dest-visual"><img src="/images/daytrip-shopping.jpg" alt="Maasai craft market in Arusha, Tanzania" width="800" height="500" loading="lazy"><span class="trip-price">From $70 Per person</span></div>
        <div class="dest-body">
          <div class="dest-tags"><span class="dest-tag">Arusha</span><span class="dest-tag">Day Trip</span></div>
          <h3 class="dest-name">Arusha Shopping Tour</h3>
          <p class="dest-desc">Dive directly into the vibrant colors, scents, and sounds of Arusha, the undisputed safari capital of East Africa. Guided by a trusted local expert, this urban day tour takes you beyond the tourist traps into bustling local markets, artisanal craft co-ops, and fair-trade cultural centers to find authentic Tanzanian treasures.</p>
          <a href="/daytrips/arusha-shopping-tour" class="dest-cta" style="margin-top:14px;display:inline-flex">See full itinerary &amp; details &#x2192;</a>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
